Archive Guide
1
Open your browser and navigate to: "https://IP_Data_Collector/". You can also use
the a4conf icon on the Data Collector desktop.
2
Click "Archive" within the main menu.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 2
3
The purpose of this page is to note down problems or anything else you'd like to
remember about the a4GATE you're managing. Click on a line of the "Archive" tab
to expand it and view its "Contents".
4
Click the "Add" button to add a new entry to the tab.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 3
5
Enter the title in the "Title" field.
6
Fill in the "Content", this can be a short description or anything you want to note.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 4
7
Click the "Save" button.
8
Click the "Modify" button to modify an existing entry.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 5
9
You can only modify the "Content" field. If you want to modify the "Title" you need
to create a new object.
10
Click the "Save" button.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 6
11
Click the "Delete" button to delete the object.
12
Click the "Reload" icon to refresh the list.
